## Problem
B069 survey: Vosk small en-us mangles product wake names (`hark`→hook/hawk, `herald`→harold). Alias/learning papers over weak open-vocab ASR. **Sherpa-ONNX open-vocab KWS** (English GigaSpeech 3.3M int8) matched all 7 current live wake fixtures correctly at RTF≈0.02 and ~half Vosk RSS.

See `docs/plans/B069-local-stt-survey.md`.

## Goal
Ship optional ambient wake engine `sherpa_kws` implementing `WakeBackend`, without flipping the default off Vosk until dogfood.

## Scope
- Optional dependency / download script for `sherpa-onnx-kws-zipformer-gigaspeech-3.3M-2024-01-01` (int8)
- Build keywords file from `WakePolicy` (names×prefixes + exact phrases); rebuild on config watch / SIGHUP
- `engine = "sherpa_kws"` in `[ambient]`; doctor readiness when selected
- Fixture tests (optional mark if model missing), keep text-path tests engine-agnostic
- Preserve fail-open: missing model → clear error / fall back path documented

## Non-goals
- Multi-engine UI
- Replacing cloud STT
- Training custom models

## Acceptance
- [ ] Can enable Sherpa KWS via config and wake on hey hark / hey herald live
- [ ] Keyword set follows configured names/phrases without process restart (or with existing reload)
- [ ] Vosk remains default; docs updated (AUDIO_DESIGN / CUSTOM_WAKE brief note)
- [ ] Tests + survey cross-link

Depends on: B069 survey (docs landed).


## Setup + persona defaults (dogfood, 2026-07-14)

Fold first-run / Mode A setup into this work so Sherpa is choosable at install time,
not only via hand-edited config.

### Product defaults (ship with B070 or same PR)

| Role | Wake name | Default TTS voice (xAI) |
|------|-----------|-------------------------|
| Feminine (default) | **Iris** | **eve** |
| Masculine | **Mercury** | **leo** |
| Product aliases | hark, herald | — |

- Dogfood: **Mercury** was the only masculine name that Vosk recognized first-try among
  Hermes/Apollo/etc.; **leo** chosen as default male voice after xAI sample review.
- Operator may pick **any** TTS voice from the active provider catalog
  (`hark providers voices` / OpenAI / MiniMax when auth available).
- Code: `DEFAULT_WAKE_NAMES = (iris, mercury, hark, herald)`; `[tts] voice = eve`.

### First-time guided setup — `hark setup` (full CLI)

Not agent-chat-only. Implement a **guided setup command** that:

1. Writes/updates `~/.config/hark/config.toml`
2. Writes **`~/.local/state/hark/setup-complete.json`** (or adjacent) with at least:
   - `hark_version` (the version that produced the flag)
   - `completed_at`
   - answers snapshot (wake engine, names, voice, sessions summary — no secrets)
3. On later runs / Mode A start: if flag missing **or** `hark_version` is older than
   current in a way that adds new setup questions → re-prompt only the **new** questions.

### Setup question order (logical)

Record the canonical agent+CLI script in **`skill/hark/SETUP.md`** (mirror
`packages/ultradyn-hark/skills/hark/SETUP.md`). Order:

1. Health (`hark doctor`) — text OK
2. **Herdr sessions** — local / SSH / mix
3. **Persona** — feminine (Iris+eve) vs masculine (Mercury+leo) vs custom name
4. **TTS voice** — list available voices for chosen/auto provider; play short sample optional
5. **Wake backend** — **Vosk** vs **Sherpa KWS** (vs any future engines); recommend Sherpa
   when model download is OK; Vosk if constrained; allow defer
6. Download/install model if Sherpa selected; set `[ambient] engine`
7. Confirm wake test (“say hey iris / hey mercury”)
8. Write setup-complete flag with version
9. Arm Mode A monitors (skill continues)

Voice-first after doctor when Mode A skill drives setup (TTS questions one at a time).

### Skill-adjacent docs (required)

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `skill/hark/SETUP.md` (+ package mirror) | Question script, order, config keys written, setup-complete schema |
| `skill/hark/WAKE_STT.md` (or `LOCAL_STT.md`) | Informational: Vosk / Sherpa KWS / faster-whisper / Moonshine / etc. requirements, size, when to pick; points at `docs/plans/B069-local-stt-survey.md` |

SKILL.md links both; SETUP is the agent checklist.

### Auth for multi-provider voice pick

Discover OpenAI/MiniMax keys from CLI stores — tracked as **B076** (Codex, OpenCode,
Pi agent, MiniMax CLI). Setup must not require re-pasting keys if B076 sources work.

### Non-goals (revised)

- ~~Multi-engine UI~~ → **guided CLI + skill SETUP is in scope**; full TUI optional later
- Replacing cloud STT for utterance body
- Training custom wake models in-process (see idea I00x sampling)

### Acceptance (added)

- [ ] Defaults: names iris+mercury+hark+herald; voice eve
- [ ] `hark setup` (or documented equivalent) can set engine, names, voice, sessions
- [ ] setup-complete flag includes **hark_version**; re-asks only new questions after upgrade
- [ ] `skill/hark/SETUP.md` + STT info doc + package mirrors
- [ ] Wake backend question offers Vosk vs Sherpa (+ extensible for future)
- [ ] Masculine path sets Mercury + leo unless customized
- [ ] Feminine path sets Iris + eve unless customized
- [ ] B076 used when listing/playing OpenAI/MiniMax samples during setup